/**
 * ğŸ”¹ Express.js â€“ Complete Basic Notes
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 * 1ï¸âƒ£ Express kya hai?
 *
 * - Express.js ek **Node.js framework** hai
 * - Iska use hum **server-side web applications** aur **REST APIs** banane ke liye karte hain
 * - Ye Node.js ke upar bana hota hai
 * - HTTP server banana, routing, middleware handling ko easy bana deta hai
 *
 * Example:
 *   import express from 'express';
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 2ï¸âƒ£ express kya hai? (function / class?)
 *
 * - `express` ek **function** hai
 * - Jab hum express() call karte hain, to ek **application object** milta hai
 *
 *   const app = express();
 *
 * Breakdown:
 * - express â†’ function
 * - express() â†’ function call
 * - app â†’ object (Express Application Object)
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 3ï¸âƒ£ app kya hai?
 *
 * - `app` ek **object** hai
 * - Ye Express application ko represent karta hai
 * - Is object ke andar bahut saare methods hote hain
 *
 * Example methods:
 * - app.get()
 * - app.post()
 * - app.use()
 * - app.listen()
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 4ï¸âƒ£ express.static() kya hai?
 *
 * - `express.static()` ek **built-in middleware function** hai
 * - Ye static files ko serve karne ke kaam aata hai
 *
 * Static files ka matlab:
 * - HTML
 * - CSS
 * - JavaScript
 * - Images
 * - Fonts
 *
 * Jo files **change nahi hoti**, unhe static files bolte hain
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 5ï¸âƒ£ static ka matlab kya hota hai?
 *
 * - Static = fixed / unchanged
 * - User request kare to server direct file bhej deta hai
 * - Koi logic, database, processing nahi hoti
 *
 * Example:
 * - style.css
 * - logo.png
 * - script.js
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 6ï¸âƒ£ express.static() ka return type
 *
 * - express.static() ek **middleware function return karta hai**
 *
 *   express.static(path)
 *        â†“
 *   middleware function
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 7ï¸âƒ£ app.use() kya hai?
 *
 * - `app.use()` middleware ko register karne ke liye use hota hai
 * - Ye har incoming request pe execute hota hai
 *
 * Example:
 *   app.use(express.static('public'));
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 8ï¸âƒ£ express.static() ka syntax
 *
 *   app.use(express.static(rootPath));
 *
 * Example:
 *   app.use(express.static('public'));
 *
 * Matlab:
 * - Agar user `/style.css` request kare
 * - Express `public/style.css` file serve karega
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 9ï¸âƒ£ Real folder structure
 *
 *   project/
 *   â”œâ”€â”€ server.js
 *   â”œâ”€â”€ public/
 *   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ css/
 *   â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ style.css
 *   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ js/
 *   â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ script.js
 *   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ images/
 *   â”‚       â””â”€â”€ logo.png
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * ğŸ”Ÿ ESM ke sath express.static() (Best Practice)
 *
 *   import path from 'path';
 *   import { fileURLToPath } from 'url';
 *
 *   const __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);
 *   const __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);
 *
 *   app.use(express.static(path.join(__dirname, 'public')));
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 1ï¸âƒ£1ï¸âƒ£ express.static() internally kya karta hai?
 *
 * - Request URL ko folder ke andar file se match karta hai
 * - File mil gayi â†’ direct response bhej deta hai
 * - File nahi mili â†’ next middleware pe chala jata hai
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 * 1ï¸âƒ£2ï¸âƒ£ express.static() me class / object / method breakdown
 *
 * - express â†’ function
 * - static â†’ function (express object ka method)
 * - express.static() â†’ middleware function
 * - app.use() â†’ middleware register karne ka method
 *
 * ------------------------------------------
 *
 *   One-line summary:
 *
 * - Express â†’ Node.js framework
 * - express â†’ function
 * - app â†’ object
 * - express.static() â†’ middleware function
 * - static files â†’ HTML, CSS, JS, images
 * - app.use() â†’ middleware lagane ka method
 */
